{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/claude-directory.md#clear-local-data", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/claude-directory.md", "anchor": "clear-local-data", "breadcrumb": "Explore the .claude directory > Application data > Clear local data", "level": 3, "position": 10, "text": "You can delete any of the application-data paths above at any time. New sessions are unaffected. The table below shows what you lose for past sessions.\n\nDon't delete `~/.claude.json`, `~/.claude/settings.json`, or `~/.claude/plugins/`: those hold your auth, preferences, and installed plugins.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/claude-directory.md#application-data", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/claude-directory.md#application-data", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/claude-directory.md", "anchor": "application-data", "breadcrumb": "Explore the .claude directory > Application data", "level": 2, "position": 6, "text": "Beyond the config you author, `~/.claude` holds data Claude Code writes during sessions. These files are plaintext. Anything that passes through a tool lands in a transcript on disk: file contents, command output, pasted text.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
